headline: LOW Q3 Deep Dive: Pro Business, Digital Growth, and Acquisition Integration Shape Outlook
summary: Home improvement retailer Lowe’s (NYSE:LOW) met Wall Streets revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 3.2% year on year to $20.81 billion. The company’s outlook for the full year was close to analysts’ estimates with revenue guided to $86 billion at the midpoint. Its non-GAAP profit of $3.06 per share was 3.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
